SWISS DAYBOOK: Nestle Names CFO; Actelion Shareholder Elliott

-- B y   C o r i n n e   G r e t l e r
-- 
2011-09-28T05:39:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/swiss-daybook-nestle-names-cfo-actelion-shareholder-elliott.html
Nestle SA (NESN) , the world’s biggest food
company, named Wal-Mart Stores Inc. executive Wan Ling Martello
as chief financial officer to succeed Jim Singh.  EQUITIES:
*Actelion’s board elected Jean-Pierre Garnier as chairman,
replacing Cawthorn; Elliott, shareholder group holds less than 3
percent
*Private bankers’ Asian pay surge poised to slow, Falcon CEO
says
*Basel Committee said to keep capital-surcharge plans for banks
*UBS sues highland crusader for $686 million in New York
*Syngenta loses court bid against Bunge over modified corn  ECONOMY/GOVERNMENT:
*SNB’s Thomas Jordan speaks in Basel at 6:15 p.m.  MARKETS:
*The SMI rose 3 percent to 5,564.62
*The SPI gained 3.1 percent to 5,050.99
*The Stoxx Europe 600 Index climbed 4.4 percent to 229.91
*The MSCI Asia-Pacific Index was up 0.4 percent at 7:27 a.m.
Zurich time
